<item>
            <title>[HBASE-8756] Add open regions for writes without waiting on log replay in current distributed log splitting scheme</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8756</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;distributed log replay would add opening regions to take writes before waiting on distributed log replay to finish.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can add this facility to our current distributed log splitting mechanism too?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Depends on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8741&quot; title=&quot;Scope sequenceid to the region rather than regionserver (WAS: Mutations on Regions in recovery mode might have same sequenceIDs)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-8741&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-8741&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; or something like it so our sequenceids are good when the region opens.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
