                            <comment id="13698462" author="aleksshulman" created="Wed, 3 Jul 2013 00:53:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this item is covered as part 2 of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7006&quot; title=&quot;[MTTR] Improve Region Server Recovery Time - Distributed Log Replay&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7006&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7006&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Can I dupe this one out, or is there more to this than what is in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7006&quot; title=&quot;[MTTR] Improve Region Server Recovery Time - Distributed Log Replay&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7006&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7006&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13698583" author="stack" created="Wed, 3 Jul 2013 04:24:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aleksshulman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aleksshulman&quot;&gt;Aleksandr Shulman&lt;/a&gt; This is different.  This is enabling writes with our current WAL splitting mechanism (&quot;distributed log splitting&quot; as opposed to &quot;distributed log replay&quot;, the new mechanism).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13728633" author="stack" created="Sat, 3 Aug 2013 20:33:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving improvement out of 0.95/0.96&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
